        <hl1>Compete With China</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Educated Giant,'' by Nicholas D. Kristof (column, May 28):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Educated Giant,'' by Nicholas D. Kristof (column, May 28):</p>
        <p>When I was little, parents all over said: ''Eat everything on your plate. There are children starving in Africa.'' Today we say to our kids: ''Eat everything on your plate, then go study. There are children starving in Africa, and the kids in China are studying like crazy.''</p>
        <p>We shouldn't see China as a threat. Instead, China's commitment to learning, technology and growth is a challenge for the United States to step it up, work a little harder and learn a little more.</p>
        <p>The world is a competitive place. This could be very good for us.</p>
        <p>Ned Farquhar  Albuquerque, May 28, 2007</p>
      </block>
